@chinmaygarde 
Is there any way to send event log or error when flickering occurred on customer's devices?
We would like to measure flickering occurrence probability if possible.

Hello @zanderso 

The app is currently running on version 3.0.

I'm sorry, I tried to reproduce the issue on a fresh 3.0 install on an iPhone 12 (15.6.1), but nothing... 
The "good" news is that QA members of my team can reproduce it 100% (see scenario from previous comment) from DEV build (on 3.0) BUT it seems that the bug occurs from our use of the inappwebview [package](https://pub.dev/packages/flutter_inappwebview) because I can't get it on a new flutter project.

Also, sorry but I can't provide the project I am working on. It is a commercial app (in production) of a big european company. ☹️

I only can show this... but I don't think it could help, and it looks like crashlytics doesn't catch any logs from this issue...

```
InAppWebView(
                key: _key,
                initialOptions: state.options,
                onWebViewCreated: onWebViewCreated,
                onUpdateVisitedHistory: controller.historyChange,
                onLoadStart: (_, uri) => controller.onLoadStart(uri),
                onLoadStop: (_, uri) => controller.onLoadStop(uri),
                onLoadError: (_, uri, code, message) => controller.onLoadError(uri, code, message),
                androidOnPermissionRequest: (controller, origin, resources) async {
                  return PermissionRequestResponse(resources: resources, action: PermissionRequestResponseAction.GRANT);
                },
                shouldOverrideUrlLoading: (controller, navigationAction) async {
                  return NavigationActionPolicy.ALLOW;
                },
                onConsoleMessage: (_, message) {
                  if (kDebugMode) {
                    print(message);
                  }
                },
              )
```
